JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 1719
EP  - 1747
VL  - 48
IS  - 5
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1993.tb05126.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT This paper uses a nonlinear arbitrage-pricing model, a conditional linear model, and an unconditional linear model to price international equities, bonds, and forward currency contracts. Unlike linear models, the nonlinear arbitrage-pricing model requires no restrictions on the payoff space, allowing it to price payoffs of options, forward contracts, and other derivative securities. Only the nonlinear arbitrage-pricing model does an adequate job of explaining the time series behavior of a cross section of international returns.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Measuring and Testing the Impact of News on Volatility
AU  - ENGLE, ROBERT F.
AU  - NG, VICTOR K.
Y1  - 1993/12/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/12/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1993.tb05127.x
