PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1993.tb05135.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT We develop a simple model in which the presence of portfolio insurers in a market of risk-averse traders leads to multiple equilibria for the pricing of financial assets and can cause an increase in volatility, including insurance-induced price drops. We demonstrate, however, that centralized portfolio insurance firms may actually reduce, not increase, volatility, even if the existence of these firms increases the total amount of funds under insurance.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Why Option Prices Lag Stock Prices: A Trading-based Explanation
AU  - CHAN, KALOK
AU  - CHUNG, Y. PETER
AU  - JOHNSON, HERB
Y1  - 1993/12/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/12/01
